Package com.cloudhopper.mc.generator.generic.annotations

Annotationsschnittstelle Template

@Retention(SOURCE) @Target({}) public @interface Template
Describes a single template to be rendered by the GenericDeploymentConfigGenerator.

The output location, file type, and rendering phase are all controlled via this annotation.

  • Erforderliche Elemente - Übersicht

    Erforderliche Elemente
    Modifizierer und Typ
    Erforderliches Element
    Beschreibung
    String
    outputFileExtension
    The file extension to apply to the rendered output (e.g., "tf", "json", "java").
    com.cloudhopper.mc.generator.api.GenerationPhase
    phase
    The generation phase in which this template should be executed.
    String
    templateName
    The name of the template file (without the file extension).

    • phase

      com.cloudhopper.mc.generator.api.GenerationPhase phase
      The generation phase in which this template should be executed.

    • templateName

      String templateName
      The name of the template file (without the file extension).

      For example, if you provide "function", the system will look for function.ftl in the generator's template folder.

      Gibt zurück:
      the template base name

    • description

      A short description of the template's purpose.

      the template description

    • outputFileExtension

      The file extension to apply to the rendered output (e.g., "tf", "json", "java").
      Gibt zurück:
      the output file extension

    • outputSubDirectory

      String outputSubDirectory
      The relative subdirectory where this file should be written (e.g., "deployment/aws"). If empty, the file is written to the root output directory.
      Gibt zurück:
      the output subdirectory
      Standard:
      ""

    • javaFile

      boolean javaFile
      Whether the rendered output is a Java source file. If true, the processor will integrate it into the Java compilation process.
      Gibt zurück:
      true if the template generates a Java file
      Standard:
      false
